docs.lead_paragraph: One morning last week, President Trump went after the “dirty cops,” as he has called them in the past, complaining that “Police Organizations & National Security Organizations were used to SPY on a Campaign.” Sixty-one minutes later, he was extolling officers as heroes and vowing to stop anyone who wants to defund “our great Police.”
